# Architecture Rules - Forkumentos

## Feature-First Design
All files must adhere to the Feature-First architecture structure:
- **lib/app/**: App-wide entry point, global configurations.
- **lib/core/**: Core system layers (commands, constants, errors, extensions, services, theme, utils). Core should not depend on features or shared.
- **lib/features/**: Contain individual feature modules (project, template, datasource, mapping, preview, review, export, settings). Features are self-contained.
- **lib/shared/**: Shared UI widgets, dialogs, enums, models, and providers used across multiple features.
- **lib/routing/**: Navigation and routing declarations using `go_router`.

## Dependency Flow Rules
- Feature folders must be self-contained. Avoid tight coupling between features.
- Communication between features must go through shared interfaces, providers, or routing.
- Do not import code from other features directly unless it is a sub-feature or explicitly designed module communication.
- Core and Shared layers must never depend on any feature.
